<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78a144f5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s330d"><num value="330d">§ 330d.</num><heading> Violation; penalty</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any person who knowingly and willfully violates <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s330a">section 330a of this title</ref>, or any rule issued thereunder, shall upon conviction thereof be fined not more than $10,000.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78a144f6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/92/205/s5">Pub. L. 92–205, § 5</ref>, <date date="1971-12-18">Dec. 18, 1971</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/85/736">85 Stat. 736</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
